<div class="section" id="calwin">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>CalWin Instructions</h1>
    <ol>
      <li><p>Explain at intake about optional Text & Email messaging service.</p></li>
      <li><p>Ask clients to sign Agreement to Receive Optional Text Messaging & Email Service form to indicate that the process was explained; if they consent to one or both parts, collect information.  Give client a copy of the form and keep a copy to send to I-Files.</p></li>
      <li><p>Update CalWIN’s...</p>
        <ul>
          <li><p>Case Information: In the Case Summary Information tab, add the client’s cell phone number in the Message Number field. Add email in the E-mail field. <strong>If this is done in Demographics tab of CalWIN, then clients will NOT receive the messages.</strong></p></li>
          <li><p>Add Case Special Indicators: In the Display Demographic Summary Tab > Collect Individual Demographics Detail, add the following special indicators that apply:
            <ol>
              <li><p>Text Messages OK <strong>and/or</strong></p></li>
              <li><p>B) Email Ok.</p></li>
            </ol>
          If a client wishes to terminate messages, update effective end date with the current date.</p></li>
        </ul>
      <li><p>Please send that paper copy to I-Files!</p></li>
    </ol>

    <p class="thanks">Special thanks to Michelle Berry at Medi-Cal for putting most of this together.</p>

  </div>
